#31219
the North Star Artery~
   The land surrounding the road has becoming increasingly barren as this road
to the north.  It seems that the surrounding wildlife is almost non-existant
or hiding underground.  The air is harshly dry and cold.  The road south
beckons you as it surely is more comfortable and warm.  To the east, as well
as the west, the ground is still showing signs of life, but has small patches
of snow clinging on.  
~
