#31225
Approaching the Frjosa Bridge~
   The cobblestone road has come to an end here and a dull black stone walkway
has taken over towards the north.  Looking north you will see a very long
bridge made of this same black stone.  It is mostly covered in ice and snow
and looks treacherous albeit not as bad as trying to pass through that river
beneath it.  There are exits in all four cardinal directions.  West and east,
the tundra, south will bring you to the open road, and north the bridge to the
white abyss of the north.  
~
