#31242
On the Eastern Shoulder of the N. Star Artery~
   The shoulder is about as wide as two grown men are tall.  The ground is
covered with a thick blanket of pine straw.  This is where travelers will stop
and camp when the need arises.  The forest tree line is to the east.  To the
north, as far as you can see, the road shoots straight north and this shoulder
follows.  To the south the road and shoulder continue towards the city of Kir
Drax'in.  To the west you can get back on the main road.  
~
