#31288
Along the Northern Wall of Kir Drax'in~
   The land closest to the wall is mostly cleared of any large trees or
structures.  This is to minimize anyone using the tall pines to give a line of
sight into the city from above.  The ground is covered in mostly grass and
pine straw.  To the north the woods become more dense and lush with
vegitation.  Looking south you find the solid stone and steel reinforced walls
of the bustling city.  Going back east will bring you back to the beginning of
the North Star Artery.  West the wall continues on.  
~
